definition: king or monarch/best or strongest of its type/grand/great

son/child/seed/egg/small thing/1st earthly branch: 11 p.m.-1 a.m., midnight, 11th solar month (7th December to 5th January), year of the Rat/Viscount, fourth of five orders of nobility 五等爵位[wu3 deng3 jue2 wei4]/ancient Chinese compass point: 0° (north)

pinyin: Ai4 de2 hua2 Wang2 zi3 Dao3

sentences.english: But the little prince made no reply.
"I've lost her, " said the Prince, and he returned sadly to the palace.
sentences.chinese: “我把她給追丟了，”王子傷心地回了王宮。

sentences.english: Then you truly are a fool, Prince Frog.
sentences.chinese: 那你就着實是個傻瓜，青蛙王子。

sentences.english: When is the prince marrying the princess?
sentences.chinese: 王子什麼時候把公主娶回家？

sentences.english: And prince Siddhartha became the "Buddha" in eastern India.
sentences.chinese: 悉達多王子在印度東部成爲“佛陀”。

sentences.english: I hope my future prince charming has such a personality.
sentences.chinese: 我希望自己未來的白馬王子也具備這樣的個性。

sentences.english: Then he put a poison arrow in his bow and shot it straight at the monster.
sentences.chinese: 而後王子將毒箭放在弓上，對直朝怪物射去。

sentences.english: I met a prince, Fairy Godmother.
sentences.chinese: 我遇到了一個王子，精靈教母。

sentences.english: Consider the recent opening of the new, expanded Fairview Container Terminal at the Port of Prince Rupert.
sentences.chinese: 最近在魯伯特王子島港新開通了怡景集裝箱轉運站。

sentences.english: She was the first wife of HRH The Prince Charles, Prince of Wales.
sentences.chinese: 她是威爾士王子查爾斯的第一任妻子。

sentences.english: In her, led by Prince Albert also bought a Patek Philippe table.
sentences.chinese: 在她所領導的阿爾伯特王子也買了百達翡麗表。

sentences.english: Prof Wang Zihao, the president of BUCT hosted the welcome reception.
sentences.chinese: 王子鎬校長出席了歡迎晚宴並祝酒。

sentences.english: The wedding of Prince Edouard and his bride was a far more low-key affair however with only a few hundred people turning out onto the streets to watch them.
sentences.chinese: 愛德華王子的婚禮低調得多，僅有幾百人沿街觀看。

sentences.english: It's for the British prince and his fiancee.
sentences.chinese: 這是英國王子和他的未婚妻。

sentences.english: He too was went away disappointed.
sentences.chinese: 這位王子也十分傷心地離開了。

sentences.english: But, do what they would, their noses were nothing in comparison with the Prince's.
sentences.chinese: 可不管他們怎麼費力，都遠不能與王子的鼻子相比。

definition: lit. little princess/fig. spoiled girl/female version of 小皇帝[xiao3 huang2 di4]
